Task one: install node js

what is node.js?

Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform runtime environment for developing server-side web applications.
Node.js applications are written in JavaScript.
It allows executing JavaScript programs on desktop machines. 
It is commonly used to create server side networking applications. 
In this course Node.js will be used to implement HTTP servers that will host HTML content and RESTful Web services.

1. download node js and install from https://nodejs.org/en/
2. write a hello.js (console.log("hello");) file and run it via node from windows cmd


Task two: using npm

what is npm?
npm is the default Package manager for the JavaScript runtime environment Node.js

1. initializing Node.js projects:
-- visiting https://www.npmjs.com/, there are many frameworks.
2. initializing node.js package
-- on cmd window do npm init
-- package.json is the standard name of NPM

https://docs.nodejitsu.com/articles/getting-started/npm/what-is-npm


Task three: setting up openshift
1. visit https://www.openshift.com/
2. create account on openshift and create a nodejs application
3. install openshift client tools 
https://developers.openshift.com/en/getting-started-windows.html#client-tools

Step 1: Install Ruby with RubyInstaller
(http://rubyinstaller.org/downloads/)
Step 2: Install Git version control
(https://git-for-windows.github.io/)
Step 3: Install the rhc Ruby gem
(C:\> gem install rhc)

4. generate the key C:\> rhc setup
4.1 git clone ssh:key
4.2 npm install (install the express dependencies)
4.3 change local index.html file
4.4 create .gitigore file by c:> echo node_modules > .gitignore
4.5 git add . // git commit -am "change index.html" // git push origin

5 change server.js file to use express
http://expressjs.com/

6. run c:> node server.js to show how to use localhost
7. demo changes on localhost and openshift


-- git  add <filename>
-- git rm --cached <filename>
-- git commit -am "changes to openshift"
-- git push origin


Task four: setting up git account
1. create account in https://github.com/
2. download and install git client: https://git-scm.com/download/win


Task five: setup github remote for local changes
1. add github remote repo: git remote add github <git-hub url>
2. git push -u github master


Conclusion
JavaScript is a language written for websites to run in the clientâ€™s browser.

AJAX is a way for JavaScript to request data from a server without refreshing the page or blocking the application.

jQuery is a JavaScript library built to automate and simplify common web tasks like AJAX or animation.

Angular is a hip JavaScript framework which is made for building large, single-page web applications.

Node.js allows JavaScript to be run without a browser, and is commonly used to run web servers.

A single-page application (SPA) is a web application or web site that fits on a single web page with the goal of providing a more fluid user experience akin to a desktop application.
